stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Start
    Start --> ReadCurrentFile : read workflow-delegation.md

    ReadCurrentFile --> InsertFormatRules : current content parsed
    ReadCurrentFile --> End_Error : file not found

    InsertFormatRules --> AddContaminationGuard : format rules inserted into templates
    InsertFormatRules --> InsertFormatRules : missing section, retry insertion

    AddContaminationGuard --> VerifyLineCount : guard clause added to Constraints block
    AddContaminationGuard --> AddContaminationGuard : guard text conflicts with existing line

    VerifyLineCount --> End : line count <= 200
    VerifyLineCount --> SplitFile : line count > 200

    SplitFile --> VerifyLineCount : re-check after extraction
    SplitFile --> End_Error : cannot reduce below 200

    End --> [*]
    End_Error --> [*]

%% ## decisions
%%
%% - state granularity: 6 named states (Start through End) -- each maps to one discrete edit action, preventing combined steps that hide failures
%% - ReadCurrentFile as explicit state: separates file I/O from transformation logic -- allows distinct error path when file is missing or unreadable
%% - InsertFormatRules before AddContaminationGuard: format rules must exist before the guard references them -- guard clause says "Format: Markdown" which is part of the inserted rules
%% - self-loop on InsertFormatRules: accounts for partial insertion when template sections differ between Template A/B/C -- retry within same state avoids state explosion
%% - VerifyLineCount as gate: 200-line constraint is a hard rule from core-constraints.md -- must be checked after all insertions, not during
%% - SplitFile recovery path: if line count exceeds 200 after edits, extract supplementary content to a separate file -- maintains core-constraints compliance without losing content
%% - End_Error terminal: two failure paths (file not found, cannot reduce lines) both terminate without partial changes -- prevents half-applied edits from corrupting the delegation template
%% - no rollback state: git provides rollback; adding an explicit rollback state duplicates VCS capability -- keeps diagram focused on forward progress
